This paper discusses the challenges of data trading and proposes a solution that integrates truthfulness and privacy preservation. The paper involves techniques such as encryption, signature, and batch verification, which are commonly used in the field of cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed solution also deals with data processing and outcome verification, which are relevant to databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the evaluation of the proposed solution on datasets, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
